Virgin Galactic Logo
Virgin Galactic is a spaceflight company that operates in, and is incorporated in, the United States. It was founded by Richard Branson and his British Virgin Group retains a 24% stake. It is developing commercial spacecraft and aims to provide suborbital spaceflights to space tourists. Virgin Galactic’s suborbital spacecraft are air launched from beneath a carrier airplane known as White Knight Two. Virgin Galactic’s founder, Richard Branson, had originally hoped to see a maiden spaceflight by 2010, but the date was delayed for several years, primarily due to the October 2014 crash of VSS Enterprise due to a pilot error.
You can download theVirgin Galacticlogo on full-version of the page.
